<br>
Eliani loved the Twilight Sea. She loved having all those elementals around. Slaini swore that the earh elementals smelled but Eliani had never smelled such a thing as a bad smell from them. The Twilight Sea was far from home. Up on the moon actually. But it made for a good camp. They had access to portals everywhere and yet could do some decent hunting at very close range. Or had been able to... Lately they were having to travel farther and farther to hunt anything that gave them experience. Eliani was so glad they had abandoned the idea of making camp in the Western Wastes. Cold was not her thing. Right now most of the Elite were home. The guild hall was more full than it had ever been before. <br>
<br>
She wondered where they could go. The Plane of Knowledge was too civilized for a camp such as this. And as for civilization, the guild hall in Kelethin was plenty civilized enough for the Elite. Tunare would provide. <br>
<br>
Just then Ariaa ran in. &quot;I just ported Aryllyian back here. Yep he's had too much to drink again.&quot; Eliani laughed at Ariaa and went to help her. <br>
<br>
&quot;What say we take off his armor and leave him tied up somewhere&quot; Ariaa asked mischeviously. Eliani readily agreed to help. <br>
<br>
They got him undressed enough that he could sleep comfortably and waited for him to begin to snore again. Eillail walked in to check on him just as they finished. <br>
<br>
&quot;What are you two evildoers up to?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;We are just helping Ary, E. He'll be fine. Ariaa ported him home drunk. He's tired and disheartened and we are just taking care of him.&quot; They looked at him innocently.<br>
<br>
&quot;I know, I have been worried, too&quot; Eillail said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well life here isn't easy. It gets you down&quot; Ariaa agreed. <br>
<br>
Eliani said, &quot;We are looking after him, you can go read.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I was just on my way to do that, how did you know?&quot;<br>
<br>
Eliani laughed and pointed to the book in Eillail's hands. He looked down and laughed with her. &quot;Oh...&quot; he said, and wandered off. <br>
<br>
Aryllyian continued to snore soundly. When Eillail left, Ariaa and Eliani tied his left arm to the low table beside his bed and left him. <br>
<br>
The laughed and went into the kitchen. Eliani had several things baking. &quot;He'll wonder how he got in that position and be too polite to ask, just like always.&quot; They had a good laugh.<br>
<br>
Eliani felt a bit of remorse. What they had done wasn't nice. She waited till Ariaa left and thought about undoing him. She'd tell Irislilly what happened and that would ease her mind. She hunted down Iris and hugged her, pulling her from the armor repair she was doing. &quot;Come with me, I need to speak to you quietly.&quot;<br>
<br>
Iris followed Eliani to the kitchen. She was curious. <br>
&quot;What did you do, my elvish friend.?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;It wasn't just me, it was mainly Ariaa's idea.&quot; Eliani told her the details. Iris laughed and laughed. <br>
<br>
&quot;Oh I can help with this one. I'll be right back.&quot; <br>
<br>
Iris reappeared several minutes later. <br>
Eliani looked up, &quot;What did you do, Iris the Evil?&quot;<br>
<br>
Iris just shook her head. &quot;Wait and see....&quot;<br>
<br>
