She tried not to think of it but it did bother her that he went so often to Seyah for comfort when he was troubled.  <br>
&quot;Well,&quot; she sighed &quot;they both share such a deep love for their Mother Tunare, it is only natural.&quot;  <br>
Just then she smacked her thumb with the smithy hammer and cursed softly under her breath. <br>
She heard the rustle of silk and turn to see Eliani standing there head down. Irislilly called upon Quellious to grant Eliani some peace, and went to her.<br>
&quot;Come with me, sister&quot; Eliani said.  &quot;I have been up to mischief.&quot; <br>
Upon hearing her tale Irislilly threw back her head and laughed.  This would be a great opportunity to lighten things up around here. Elves were supposed to be lighthearted maybe a good practical joke would help them all to remember that.  <br>
&quot;Wait here.  I will take care of this,&quot; she said.<br>
Quietly she crept into the main hall seeing noone about she snatched up a quill and a parchment from the writing table.  As she turned to leave something caught her eye...that will be perfect she thought and picked up Seyahs comfy blanket from her chair by the fire.<br>
A few minutes later Iris appeared again in the kitchen.  &quot;Come here Elfy and see what I have done,&quot; she grinned.<br>
She led Eliani back to Arys room where he remained snoring and tied to the bedside table. She had removed his pants and he slept there in nothing but his shirt and *braise.  Clutched tightly in his other hand he held Seyahs afghan.  Pinned to which was a note which read: &quot; Ary, Lets keep this our secret.  I have a reputation to uphold, I am a nun after all.  Seyah&quot;<br>
Eliani gasped in surprise and then began to chuckle,&quot;that should cause some interesting fallout.  Let's go eat some cookies&quot;<br>
