<br>
&quot;Okay ladies, what's up?&quot; Ariaa said, pouring wine. She was still panting from carrying the snoring Slaini home. <br>
<br>
&quot;You look tired, Ariaa&quot; Eliani noticed.<br>
<br>
&quot;I am beat. I found her in Freeport at the Green Jade Inn. They sent a bard with a note to me in the commons. I was getting batwings. So I went to the inn, picked her up and ported here.&quot; She looked around, &quot;Can you help me with Slaini, please? I don't think I can get her to her room.&quot;<br>
<br>
Irislilly and Eliani burst into laughter again and wandered off. Ariaa wondered what they had done. She wondered if Aryllyian had woken up. Maybe she'd peek in on him. She dragged Slaini to just outside his doorway and had to stop for breath. Slaini had to stop drinking or get herself home, that was all there was to it. She looked down. &quot;Slaini, you have to stop this, Hon.&quot;<br>
<br>
Slaini only gurgled some unintelligable response. Ariaa had to pick up everyone from a raid in less than half an hour. No one would be here but Iris and Eliani. She'd tell them to move Slaini the rest of the way if they had time. She dragged Slaini into Ary's room and took off the heavy armor. Slaini groaned at her and curled up into a ball. She didn't want poor Slaini to be cold and was out of time. So she scooted Slaini next to Aryllyian and covered her with Seyah's afghan. <br>
<br>
&quot;I hope Seyah doesn't come home and want to get comfy&quot; she thought. Either way, she didn't have time to do anything else. She took Slaini's armor and pack and dropped them into her room. Slaini would wonder too, now. <br>
<br>
Ariaa ran to the kitchen and told Iris and Eliani where she was headed. She didn't remember to explain that Slaini was in Ary's room until she was teleporting and gone. They'd figure it out...<br>
<br>
<br>
