<br>
Poor Slaini, Seyah thought, being guildleader really had unhinged her, and that was months ago.  She pushed the door open, intending to move Slaini to the bed.   But the bed was occupied.  Seyah stopped, trying to comprehend what she saw.  <br>
<br>
Ary had one arm tied to the table.  &quot;What is that supposed to accomplish?&quot; Seyah wondered, totally mystified.  &quot;Either tie both arms or none, but why *one*??&quot; She looked again at Slaini, and noticing her own afghan, she made a face and reached down to collect it.  The crackle of parchment attracted her attention and she unpinned the note.   Her eyebrows shot up and she looked sternly again at Slaini, still snoring.   It didn't look like Slaini's handwriting.  She tucked the note into her bracer, to save for the fire.<br>
<br>
Again she looked at Aryllyian, and froze.  His eyes were open, and he was looking at his arm tied to the table, and then at her in question.   She felt a flush start at her collar bone and rise through her neck to the roots of her hair, leaving her cheeks flaming with heat.<br>
<br>
&quot;Your pardon, Aryllyian, I didn't mean to intrude,&quot; she stammered, glancing at the inert form at her feet. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/belvenelite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seyahmt>SeyahMT</A> at: 11/1/02 8:24:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#BA9F70><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/belvenelite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=firinn>Firinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Raid Leader / BFB</span><br>  Posts: 305<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(11/2/02 1:11:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The never ending story</span><hr size=1> Firinn, still a little bleary, emerges from his room with scraps of the note he had written to Ivri in his hand, wondering how he had missed them the night before.  Walking down the hallway, he notices Aryllyian's door is open and Seyah standing inside the doorway.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey, anyone got anything to eat?!&quot;<br>
<br>
Seyah turns to look at him, and he notices her face is flush with a deep red, and a look of surprise on her face.  <br>
<br>
&quot;You seem to have something clinging to your armor Seyah&quot;, he says, reaching for what is no doubt a scrap of something from her latest outing.  &quot;I'll get it, its right there...&quot; he murmurs, reaching for her wrist.  <br>
<br>
Firinn frees a parchment from Seyah's bracer, and then sees over her shoulder Slaini passed out on the floor, and Aryllyian undressed, and tied to a table!<br>
<br>
&quot;What in the world?!&quot; bellows the barbarian, forgetting the parchment in his hand.  He looks at the paladin, at the elf on the floor, and then back at Seyah quizzically, who turns a darker shade of red if its at all possible.  <br>
Firinn blinks his eyes, shakes his head and says &quot;Who can figure Elves?&quot; and starts making his way to the kitchen.<br>
<br>
Seyah calls after him to stop, and remembering the parchment in his hand, turns to give it back.  He glances down and sees...<br>
&quot;Ary, Lets keep this our secret. I have a reputation to uphold, I am a nun after all. Seyah&quot;<br>
<br>
Firinn quickly looks up at Seyah, as she snatches the note from his hand, and he says flatly, &quot;I think I shoulda just stayed in bed.&quot;<br>
