Looking up into Firinn's confused face, his hair still rumpled with sleep, Seyah felt a chord of sympathy.  That was exactly how she felt.  Terribly, terribly confused.  And tired.  <br>
<br>
&quot;I didn't write this,&quot; she said, and seeing that Firinn was not really absorbing what she had said, she added, &quot;Go, have some breakfast, Sweetbear.&quot;  Seeing him turn and head toward the kitchen, she sighed and looked at the paper in her hand.  But now it was torn?  No, she had more than one paper, the note she didn't write, and some pieces. &quot;I apologize...&quot;  &quot;Paladin of tarnished armor&quot;  &quot;unseemly behavior on your part&quot;.  She opened her mouth to call the northman back for his own notes, but but shut it again since he had already stumbled out of sight.   She stood a moment, gathering her thoughts, then turned with decision back to Aryllyian and Slaini.   Ary was working at the knot that held him to the bed.   Sweeping a glance at the still unconscious Slaini, she grabbed the door handle and backed up into the hall, closing the door firmly behind her.  They were both adults, they could sort whatever that was out on their own. <br>
<br>
She marched back to her own room, tucking both the note with her forged signature and the torn pieces of the barbarian's writing into the drawer of her writing table, then began stripping her armor, hanging the pieces with decision on the armor stand by the cold hearth.   She'd been raiding for days, by the grace of the Mother, and she was filthy and tired and needed a bath.  Stripped of her armor and wearing only her shift, she lit a fire in the grate, coaxing the flames to health so that her room would be warm when she returned wet.  She sighed at the simple pleasure of a fire, feeling tranquility begin to creep back to her troubled thoughts.  Now for that bath.  She took her towel from the shelf and a clean shift, and padded barefoot back into the passage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=82.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=82.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.elvenelite.com/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.emailToFriend?topicID=82.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.threadControl?topicID=82.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=82.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a